Log storage units can be found at every balloon station. They are used to store logs, and are able to hold 100 of each type of log that is used in balloon transport. Players can interact with the log storages to store logs, change their preferences (whether the game uses logs from the storage or the player's inventory), and check the number of each log stored in the storages. The logs can be stored in noted form. Note that once logs are added they cannot be withdrawn.

'''Log storage''' units can be found at every [[Balloon transport system|balloon]] station. They are used to store logs, and are able to hold 100 of each type of log that is used in balloon transport. Players can interact with the log storages to store logs, change their preferences (whether the game uses logs from the storage or the player's inventory), and check the number of each log stored in the storages. The logs can be stored in noted form. Note that once logs are added they '''cannot be withdrawn.'''
